Chapter 2

TOOLS

QUICK FEM (C) 1997 G.PELOSI R. COCCIOLI S. SELLERI


  Directory Contents:

 +-- LIB -+-    Subroutines, from these the best thing to do is to build
 |	  |	a library, we suggest QF.LIB as name
 |        |
 |	  +- BAND.FOR     - Function to access a matrix in band storage mode
 |        +- BANDEX.FOR   - Function to estimate band occupation
 |        +- BSOLVE.FOR   - Block Solver (See Chapter 3)
 |        +- DELAUNAY.FOR - Procedure which performs Delunay regularization
 |        +- ELEE.FOR     - Functions to provide the element matrices for
 |        |                 edge elements
 |        +- ELEN.FOR     - Functions to provide the element matrices for
 |        |                 nodal elements
 |        +- FEMPS.FOR    - Subroutine to translate a FEM mesh to a PostScript
 |        |                 file
 |        +- FINDEQN.FOR  - Subroutine to find equivalent nodes in periodic
 |        |                 structure meshes
 |        +- PNJEXP.FOR   - Function to compute Basis function times exponential
 |        |                 integrals (See Chapter 3)
 |        +- READ.FOR     - Subroutine to read a mesh
 |        +- READN.FOR    - Subroutine to read a mesh, skipping edges
 |        +- RENUMBER.FOR - Subroutine to perform numbering optimization
 |        +- SOLVE.FOR    - A straightforward gauss solver for banded matrices
 |        +- WRITE.FOR    - Subroutine to write the mesh
 |        +- WRITECR.FOR  - Subroutine to write an output file for the
 |                          Post-processor
 |
 +-- MAINS -+-  Main tool programs and simple drivers for the LIB subroutines
            |
	    +- MESH.FOR    - The mesh generator
            +- POSTPRO.FOR - The post-processor
            |
	    +- DO_BEX.FOR  - Driver which estimates band of the FEM matrix 
            |         	     for a given mesh
            +- DO_DEL.FOR  - Driver for the Delunay regularization
            +- DO_F2PS.FOR - Driver for the PostScript translator
            +- DO_REN.FOR  - Driver for the numbering optimization

